"NA" Not Available. The source of data for this table, the CPS ASEC sample of 98,000 addresses, is not the official source of income and poverty estimates. Source: U.S. Census Bureau, Current Population Survey, 2014 Annual Social and Economic Supplement

Note: The 2014 CPS ASEC included redesigned questions for income and health insurance coverage. All of the approximately 98,000 addresses were eligible to receive the redesigned set of health insurance coverage questions. The redesigned income questions were implemented to a subsample of these 98,000 addresses using a probability split panel design. Approximately 68,000 addresses were eligible to receive a set of income questions similar to those used in the 2013 CPS ASEC and the remaining 30,000 addresses were eligible to receive the redesigned income questions. The source of data for this table is the CPS ASEC sample of 98,000 addresses.
